						<div class="postbody">So, I guess this is why we're talking about it, but just to be clear; if you have 16 KB of CHR-RAM, could you switch out the active portion of CHR-RAM and write to the other half outside of NMI? If so, this would seem like the ultimate solution.<br /><br />I'd even think for a low production run it could be cheaper. 16 KB of RAM is nothing these days, and a production run of a mask ROM would require high quantity and custom tooling.</div>

